def min_cost(cost, m, n):
    # Base case
    if m == 0 and n == 0:
        return 0
    # Recursive case
    if m == 0:
        return cost[0][n]
    if n == 0:
        return cost[m][0]
    # Find the minimum cost from the top left corner
    # and the bottom right corner
    left = min_cost(cost, m - 1, n)
    right = min_cost(cost, m, n - 1)
    return min(left, right) + cost[m][n]
